The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 September is 72,885 (8,400.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 September, there were 1,614 new confirmed cases (186.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 September, there were 2,293 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 30% (679 fewer cases).
